{"lemma":"خَيْرٌ","slug":"خَيْرٌ","root":"خ.#.ر","root_slug":"خ-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَيْر","root":"خير","pos":"N","occurrence_count":178},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11810"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goodness, good","examples":[{"text":"بِخَيْرٍ","english":"well"},{"text":"وَيَدْعُ ٱلْإِنْسَانُ بِٱلشَّرِّ دُعَاءَهُ بِٱلْخَيْرِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charity; welfare"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wealth; money","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"وَإِنَّهُ لِحُبِّ ٱلْخَيْرِ لَشَدِيدٌ","english":"And indeed he is, in love of wealth, intense."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant a choice, to let choose"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"better; best","examples":[{"text":"الصَّلاةُ خَيْرٌ مِن الْنَّوْمِ","english":"Prayer is better than sleep."},{"text":"لَسْتُ خَيْرًا مِن الطَّالِبِ.","english":"I am not better than the student."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"beneficent, benevolent"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xajr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11810","headword_ar":"خَيْرٌ","root":"xyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good, moral or physical; anything that is good, real"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ideal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actual"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"potential;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, being originally an inf. n., used as sing and pl.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that all desire; such as intelligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for instance,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and equity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, and so in some copies of the K;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and excellence; and what is profitable"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"useful; benefit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuyuwrN","text_ar":"خُيُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and also, accord. to the Msb, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaArN","text_ar":"خِيَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [but this latter seems to be properly pl. only of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as an epithet (see below) and as a noun denoting the comparative and superlative degrees: it may however be used as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyr","text_ar":"خير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of two kinds: namely, absolute"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyr","text_ar":"خير"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is desired in all circumstances and by every person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyr","text_ar":"خير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to one and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~","text_ar":"شرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to another; as, for instance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$d","text_ar":"شد"},{"kind":"text","text":", Er-Rághib, K:) it has this last signification, namely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, ii. 176 (S, TA) and ii. 274 and xxiv. 33 and xli. 49: or in the first and second of these instances it is thus called to imply the meaning of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property, that has been collected in a praiseworthy manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much wealth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is its meaning in the first of the instances mentioned above, agreeably with a trad. of 'Alee; and also in the Kur, c. 8: (TA:) [being used as a pl. (as well as a sing.), it may be also rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and it is also used by the Arabs to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) and has this meaning in the Kur, xxxviii. 31: (TA:) [it is often best rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune; prosperity; welfare; wellbeing; weal; happiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN qaliylu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ قَلِيلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayori","text_ar":"الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man possessing little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, good; possessing few,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, good things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whom is little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"niggardly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who does little good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ES","text_ar":"عص"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does no good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is not near to doing good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting the nonexistence of good in him. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ql","text_ar":"قل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Thus it sometimes means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN laA","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayora fiyhi","text_ar":"خَيْرَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man in whom is no good or goodness; devoid of goodness; worthless."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qil~apu xayorK","text_ar":"قِلَّةُ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poverty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"niggardliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jHd","text_ar":"جحد"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino A^aholi Alxayori waAlxiyri","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ اَهْلِ الخَيْرِ وَالخِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyrN","text_ar":"خِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaYyadaYi Alxayori waAlyumoni","text_ar":"عَلَىيَدَىِ الخَيْرِ وَاليُمْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[May it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the aid of good fortune and prosperity"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prayer used with respect to a marriage. (A 'Obeyd, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aka maA waxayorFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّكَ مَا وَخَيْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa xayorK","text_ar":"مَعَ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mayest thou meet with, or attain, good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN xayorN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"resembles an epithet [like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irN","text_ar":"خَيِّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Akh, S;) therefore the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoraAtN","text_ar":"خَيْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, Msb, *) as occurring in the Kur, lv. 70; and they do not [there] mean by it [the comparative or superlative signification of the measure]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Akh, S:) you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN xay~irN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ خَيِّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man possessing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayor","text_ar":"خَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN xayorN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN xay~irapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ خَيِّرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman excellent in beauty and disposition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irN","text_ar":"خَيِّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing much"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayor","text_ar":"خَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) applied to a man; (TA;) and in the same sense you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN xayoraY","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ خَيْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwraY","text_ar":"خُورَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyarY","text_ar":"خِيَرى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the fem. of the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and of the second, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irapN","text_ar":"خَيِّرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and the pl. [of pauc.] (of the first, TA) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaArN","text_ar":"اَخْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaArN","text_ar":"خِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Msb, K:) you say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaAru AlmaAli","text_ar":"خِيَارُ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The excellent of the camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) and in like manner you say of men &c.: (TA:) [see also below:] and the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoraAtN","text_ar":"خَيْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaArN","text_ar":"خِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraArN","text_ar":"اَشْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh,) [thus] used as an epithet: (Mgh:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used as a subst.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything excellent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the pl. thereof in this sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoraAtN","text_ar":"خَيْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurs in the Kur, ix. 89: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth,) or each, (K.) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent in beauty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irN","text_ar":"خَيِّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irapN","text_ar":"خَيِّرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent in righteousness"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or there is no difference in the opinion of the lexicologists [in general] between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irapN","text_ar":"خَيِّرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az:) accord. to Zj,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoraAtN","text_ar":"خَيْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~iraAtN","text_ar":"خَيِّرَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", both occurring in different readings of the Kur, lv. 70, signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good in dispositions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Khálid Ibn-Jembeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous in race, exalted in rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation, goodly in face, good in disposition, possessing much wealth, who, if she bring forth, brings forth a generous child:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaArN","text_ar":"خِيَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied as an epithet to a sing. subst., either masc. or fem.:] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalN","text_ar":"جَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaArN","text_ar":"خِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN xiyaArN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ خِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A he-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is excellent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent and brisk"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxotaArN","text_ar":"مُخْتَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. In the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEamaru A^abiyka Alxayoru","text_ar":"لَعَمَرُ اَبِيكَ الخَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayor","text_ar":"خَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the nom. case as an epithet of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamor","text_ar":"عَمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [so that the phrase lit. means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By the good life of thy father;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but properly it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEamoru A^abiyka","text_ar":"لَعَمْرُ اَبِيكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayori","text_ar":"الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By the life of thy good father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the like is said with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~","text_ar":"شَرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emr","text_ar":"عمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used to denote superiority: one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA xayorN mino h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا خَيْرٌ مِنْ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is better than this:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the dial. of the Benoo-'Ámir, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^axoyaru","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَخْيَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino h`*aA","text_ar":"مِنْ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$~aru","text_ar":"اَشَّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the rest of the Arabs drop the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in each case: (Msb:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^axoyaru","text_ar":"هُوَ اَخْيَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is better than thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$~aru minoka","text_ar":"اَشَّرُ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa xayorN minoka","text_ar":"هُوَ خَيْرٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N minoka","text_ar":"شَرٌّ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and, [using the dim. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuyayorN","text_ar":"خُيَيْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urayorN minoka","text_ar":"شُرَيْرٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-Buzurj, TA.) You also say, when you mean to express the signification of superiority,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnapN xayoru Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فُلَانَةٌ خَيْرُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a"},{"kind":"page_break","n":830},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woman is the best of mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapu","text_ar":"خَيْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see, however, what will be found cited hereafter from the K,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN xayoru Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ خَيْرُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a man is the best of mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but not ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaru","text_ar":"اَخْيَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[unless in the dial. of the Benoo-'Ámir]: and [it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru","text_ar":"خَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when thus used does not assume the dual form nor the pl., because it has the signification of [the measure]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": for though a poet uses the dual form, he uses it as a contraction of the dual of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~irN","text_ar":"خَيِّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayotN","text_ar":"مَيْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may~itN","text_ar":"مَيِّتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayonN","text_ar":"هَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hay~inN","text_ar":"هَيِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [but. this remark in the S is incorrect: for both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayor","text_ar":"خَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyar","text_ar":"اَخْيَر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", when used in such phrases as those to which J here refers, have pl. forms of frequent occurrence, and of which examples will be found below; and, as is said by I 'Ak (p. 239), and by many other grammarians, you may say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ayodaAni A^afoDalaA Alqawomi","text_ar":"الزَّيْدَانِ اَفْضَلَا القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ayoduwna A^afoDaluw Alqawomi","text_ar":"الزَّيْدُونَ اَفْضَلُو القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afaADilu Alqawomi","text_ar":"اَفَاضِلُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hinodu fuDolaYAln~isaA='i","text_ar":"هِنْدُ فُضْلَىالنِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.; and such concordance is found in the Kur, vi. 123; and is even said by many to be more chaste than the mode prescribed by J:] it is said in the K, that you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^axoyaru","text_ar":"هُوَ اَخْيَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru","text_ar":"خَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and when you mean the signification of superiority, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN xayorapN Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ خَيْرَةٌ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnapu xayoruhumo","text_ar":"فُلَانَةُ خَيْرُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": but [SM says,] I know not how this is; for in the S is said what is different from this, and in like manner by Z in several places in the Ksh; and what is most strange is, that the author of the K quotes in the B the passage of J [from the S], and adopts the opinion of the leading authorities [as given in the S]: (TA:) or you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnapu Alxayorapu mina AlmaroA^atayoni","text_ar":"فُلَانَةُ الخَيْرَةُ مِنَ المَرْاَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a woman is the better of the two women"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa Alxayorapu","text_ar":"هِىَ الخَيْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxiyrapu","text_ar":"الخِيرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the TA, but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxiyarapu","text_ar":"الخِيَرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxiyraY","text_ar":"الخِيرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuwraY","text_ar":"الخُورَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the last being fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaru","text_ar":"اَخْيَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuyoraY","text_ar":"خُيْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so, app., the last but one,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is the better,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K:) and [using the dim. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholihi","text_ar":"اَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa xuyayoru","text_ar":"هُوَ خُيَيْرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the best of his family"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ibn-Buzurj, TA:) one says also, to one coming from a journey,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayora maA rud~a fiY A^aholK","text_ar":"خَيْرَ مَا رُدَّ فِى اَهْلٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaAlK","text_ar":"وَمَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning May God make that with which thou comest [back] to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best of what is brought back"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the absent"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with family and property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, Meyd, TA;) or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru","text_ar":"خَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~uka xayoru rad~K","text_ar":"رَدُّكَ خَيْرُ رَدٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[may thy bringing back be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best bringing back"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa","text_ar":"مَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Meyd:) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaArN","text_ar":"اَخْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of pauc., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyaArN","text_ar":"خِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of mult., and so app. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyraAnN","text_ar":"خِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAyiru","text_ar":"اَخَايِرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaru","text_ar":"اَخْيَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaruwna","text_ar":"اَخْيَرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to rational beings: in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAyiru","text_ar":"اَخَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be a pl. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaru","text_ar":"اَخْيَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyraAnN","text_ar":"خِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is app. a mistake, probably of transcription:] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN mino xiyaAri Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ مِنْ خِيَارِ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoyaArihimo","text_ar":"اَخْيَارِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAyirihimo","text_ar":"اَخَايِرِهِمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man of the best of mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka xiyaAru h`*ihi AlA_ibili","text_ar":"لَكَ خِيَارُ هٰذِهِ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyratuhaA","text_ar":"خِيرَتُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thine are,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be, the best of these camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] alike with respect to a sing. and a pl.: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilihi","text_ar":"اـِبِلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHara xiyrapa","text_ar":"نَحَرَ خِيرَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilihi","text_ar":"اـِبِلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwrapa","text_ar":"خُورَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slaughtered the best of his camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humu AlA^axoyaruwna","text_ar":"هُمُ الاَخْيَرُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning men)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are the better,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ibn-Buzurj, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA xayora","text_ar":"مَا خَيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^axoyara","text_ar":"مَا اَخْيَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, in two places.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru baw~aA='u","text_ar":"خَيْرُ بَوَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from the Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyrobuwaA","text_ar":"خِيرْبُوَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lesser cardamom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of small grain, resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAqul~ap","text_ar":"قَاقُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common cardamom"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sweet odour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","Akh","Mgh","Lth","Az","Meyd","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}